Colombian Stocks: Interconexion Electrica, Ecopetrol, Rubiales

-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 
2011-12-02T15:38:37Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/colombian-stocks-interconexion-electrica-ecopetrol-rubiales.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:11 a.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  rose 1 percent to 13,054.02, while the
Colcap Index gained 0.8 percent to 1,588.45.  Interconexion Electrica SA (ISA)  , Latin America’s
biggest power line operator known as ISA, rose 0.9 percent to
10,900 pesos.  The company sold 300 billion pesos ($154.8 million) of
inflation-linked bonds in  Colombia , the stock exchange said in a
statement yesterday. Investor demand for the securities totaled
777 billion pesos.  Colombia, South America’s third-largest oil supplier, said
its crude production rose to an average of 965,000 barrels a day
in November. In November 2010, production was 821,000 barrels a
day, the Mines and Energy Ministry said yesterday in an e-mailed
statement.  Ecopetrol SA (ECOPETL)  , Colombia’s largest oil company,
rose 1 percent to 4,170 pesos.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PREC)  , the Toronto-based
oil producer that operates fields in Colombia, rose 2 percent to
41,400 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blake Schmidt in Bogota at 
